In addition, the holder manages his identity and can therefore remain anonymous.
The system can easily be implemented by dealers, and the latter do not need to install new terminals or computer programs.
You just need to specify an address that can be "photographed and recognized" by a phone, Pierre Noizat, who assures that he has thousands of users.
There is a general trend to consider hierarchical systems in favour of more horizontal systems.
"It will take some time for bitcoin to get through, but 2013 could be a turning point," he predicts.
By the way, the ECB's report provides for the re-evaluation of the various risks considered to be high today in the event of a success of this currency.
