The monastery of the Holy Cross in Jerusalem stands at the place where the tree from which the cross was made for the crucifixion of Jesus grew according to a Christian legend.
In Jerusalem there is also the most sacred place of the Jews - the wall of complaint, the remains of a temple that was destroyed by the Romans in 70 A.D.
Traditionally, there, people of different faiths leave papers with wishes, which then go in fulfillment.
Take a trip to the height
The ruins of the Massada fortress form the remains of the secret hiding place from enemies that Herod the Great built for his family in 25 A.D.
They are located on a rock wall in the mountains at 450 meters above sea level.
Only climbers can reach the ruins of their own power.
All the others bring an air cable car to this historic summit.
In the north of the country at 1600 to 2040 meters altitude is the famous ski resort Hermon, in which it attracts countless tourists in the winter months.
From the foot of the mountain you can get there with a shuttle bus.
The ski slopes have a total length of 45 kilometers.
According to an ancient legend, pagan gods were said to have lived on the mountain summit.
