There are almost 300 museums in this country.
On just one trip, not all of them can be visited.
But at least the five most interesting of them should be paid a visit.
Among them is once the Israel Museum not far from the Knesset (Parliament).
There ancient Qumran manuscripts or scrolls from the Dead Sea, found in Felshöhlen in the Judean desert, are stored as well as about 500 thousand archaeological and anthropological exhibits.
The Museum of Art in Tel Aviv is also worth a visit.
There the collection of works by Impressionists and Expressionists Monet, Pissaro, Renoir, Cézanne, Sisley, Matisse, Modigliani, Chagall and Picasso is exhibited.
In Akko you can visit the museum in Bad Al Basha, which houses several halls of ancient Turkish baths with sculptures of the visitors and bathers at that time.
In Caesarea you should visit the unique private Ralli Museum, where you can admire sculptures by Dali and Rodin.
There are neither museum leaders nor souvenir shops there.
Admission is free, and donations are basically rejected.
The fifth museum, namely the Holocaust Museum or Yad Vashem in Tel Aviv, tells of one of the most shocking chapters of history.
The most touching section is the monument to the children, which was built to commemorate the 1.5 million children destroyed in the concentration camps and gas chambers.
When entering the room, there is complete darkness.
Stars are sparkling.
And the names of the Jewish children and the countries in which they died are heard.
Ukraine is also mentioned there.
Do something for health
The three main recreational areas of Israel are on the shores of the Mediterranean, the Red Sea and the Dead Sea.
There are swimming pools, water parks, dolphinariums and oceanaries in each of the three places.
Amazingly, in the Red Sea, the water temperature is not below 21 °C and the air warms up to 23 °C.
The Dead Sea is even warmer and it is bathed all year round.
By the way, this unusual sea with a location of 417 meters below sea level is the deepest sea in the world.
Its turquoise blue water has a high salt content and therefore even carries non-swimmer easily on the surface.
The surrounding landscape is indescribably beautiful.
Visitors come here for treatments using salt water (natural salts) and medicinal sludge, as well as for the treatment of skin inflammation, allergies, asthma, eczema, arthritis, bronchitis, diabetes and for calming stressed nerves.
