In Jaffa you can find newlywed couples from all over Israel and even other countries at photo dates.
In Caesarea, the city of King Herod, you can roam through the Roman theatre and conquer the fortress of crusaders.
In Roman times, Caesarea was the most important city of Judea and residence of Roman governors, including Pontius Pilate.
Today evening concerts and operas are performed in the carefully restored theatre.
Destinations for tourists
If you're going to Israel, don't worry about your poor English skills: About 30% of the Israelis speak Russian.
The money in the trip is better not to take in euros, but in dollars that can simply be changed into shekels (current exchange rate: 1 dollar to 3.8 shekels).
