From the beginning, I have felt the potential that you can approach things differently.
Today, in the show business, one often copies the other.
This makes sense in its own way, as everything new is considered with caution and only after a long time is accepted.
There are only a few really unique things, and I dare claim that Tap Tap belongs to them.
The first impression the viewer usually has is of course pity; that is only natural...
But this pity is absolutely unnecessary because people with disabilities are not lonely and abandoned beings that we should regret.
It is people who are able to live and develop a full life, provided that they have the necessary means to do so.
I always say that if people with disabilities succeed, this is not only a progress for themselves, but for society as a whole.
Was it also helpful for this success that you are a strict boss, how to hear from many people?
If you want to do something good, you must not compromise in many things and you must also demand a certain discipline.
