After breaking out large sulphur stones that can weigh up to 70 kilos in total, he transports them into two bamboo baskets on his shoulders over the sloppy paths of stone.
It is only 250 meters up to the top of the volcano, which rises to a height of 2386 meters, but the exhausted carriers need more than 40 minutes to climb at the tortoise pace, keeping the balance and taking their steps carefully so that they do not slip and crash.
