"The Internet was created as a medium for searching for information, but with the appearance of these pages, the rules of the game have changed," she says.
Porras explains that academic Marc Prensky, owner of a master's title in pedagogy at Yale University and author of the "Digital Natives and Immigrants" work formed these terms for explaining the phenomenon.
The digital natives are the children and young people who have grown up with this technology.
"We are the digital immigrants to teach them where we still learn," he says.
