Hagman interpreted the role of Ewing as a corrupt, insatiable man with a charismatic smile: a staunch businessman and unfaithful husband who sought to have his alcoholic wife called Sue Ellen (Linda Gray).
"I know what to stand on the tombstone of J.R.," said Hagman in 1988.
It should be called "Here lies the honorable citizen J.R. Ewing".
This is the only business he didn't win.
